== viml ==
The vim scripting language.
Short summaray about the language:

  - supports lazily loading code (fast startup)
  - simple to understand
  - not too fast
  - some language features do not exist (true objects with inheritance etc)

Most plugins are written in this language

See also [[topic/designing-a-vim-plugin]]

== how to learn viml ==
{{{
:h eval.txt
:h usr_40.txt up to usr_45.txt
}}}

useful plugins:

== vim-dev-plugin: ==
provides completion and some hints about how to debug viml code
as well as VimLGotoLastError helper command
== autoreload: ==
must have for all plugin developpers: Reloads .vim files automatically
